Preheat your oven to 200 degrees. Cut the @red potato{1} in half lengthways (no need
to peel!) and then chop each half into six wedges. Pop your wedges on a
#baking tray{}, add a drizzle of @oil{} and season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}. Toss and then roast in your oven for ~{30%minutes}.
Turn after ~{15%minutes} to make sure they cook evenly.

Peel the @carrot{1}, remove the top and bottom and chop into ½cm chunks. Peel
and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Strip
the @rosemary{½} leaves from their stalks and chop finely. Remove the
@pistachios{25} from their shells and chop roughly.

> Tip: Don't smash the pistachios to a powder, you want nice small pieces.

Cut the @savoy cabbage{½} in half, remove the core and then cut into ½cm wide
slices. Keep to one side.

Cut the @streaky bacon rasher{4} into ½cm wide pieces. In a #large bowl{}, mix
half of your rosemary with a glug of @oil{}. Add the @pork chops{2} and mix well
to coat. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{}.
Keep to one side.

== Cranberry and Pistachio Jam ==

Next, make the cranberry and pistachio jam. Pop the @dried cranberries{60} and
@white wine vinegar{1} in a #small saucepan{} with a pinch of @?sugar{} and the
@water{175%ml}. Cook on a high heat until the water has evaporated and your
dried cranberries are soft and sticky. Stir in your pistachios and keep to one
side.

== Cabbage and Pork ==

Heat a #large frying pan{} over high heat and add a splash of @oil{}.
Cook your pork for ~{2%minutes} on each side and then transfer to a #plate{}.

> Tip: We will finish cooking it later in the oven.

Keep the heat high and add your bacon and carrot. Cook for ~{5%minutes}, stirring
frequently and then add your cabbage. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{},
then add your garlic and remaining rosemary. Cook for ~{1%minute} more and then
add the @water{50%ml}. Pop a lid on (or cover tightly with #tinfoil{}), lower the
heat to medium and cook for ~{7-10%minutes} or until your cabbage is soft.

When your wedges have ~{10%minutes} left, lay your pork on top of your wedges on
the baking tray and roast in your oven for ~{10%minutes}.

> Tip: The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

When your pork is ready, remove from your oven and leave to rest for
~{2%minutes}. Warm your cabbage, taste and add more salt and black pepper if
needed. Serve your cabbage on your plates with your wedges alongside. Pop a pork
chop on top and finish with a generous spoonful of your cranberry and pistachio
jam. Enjoy!